WEBVTT

00:02.628 --> 00:03.708
JIMMY:
Let there be cake.

00:03.879 --> 00:05.870
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

00:06.507 --> 00:08.498
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

00:09.718 --> 00:12.926
I didn't mean to cut your head off.
I'm just under a lot of pressure here.

00:13.097 --> 00:14.086
[CHLOE CHUCKLES]

00:14.264 --> 00:16.846
-Uh, who wants cake?
WOMAN: Oh, yeah, I do.

00:17.017 --> 00:19.133
Another glass of bubbly.

00:19.311 --> 00:21.427
And throw in a Shirley Temple
for the lady.

00:23.732 --> 00:26.109
Lois, don't you think
you might wanna pace yourself?

00:26.276 --> 00:29.268
Believe me, Smallville,
I am a lot more obnoxious sober.

00:29.446 --> 00:33.530
And the last thing anyone wants
is me making a scene at this blessed event.

00:34.785 --> 00:36.070
[SIGHS]

00:36.245 --> 00:38.076
Chloe is barely legal.

00:38.247 --> 00:42.957
And she is getting herself hitched to the
ﬁrst guy who's shown her any attention.

00:43.127 --> 00:45.118
Present company excepted.

00:45.295 --> 00:48.753
l have suffered enough heartache
to know real love when | see it.

00:49.633 --> 00:50.873
And looking at those two...

00:51.969 --> 00:53.379
...I don't know.

00:53.554 --> 00:54.543
[LOIS SIGHS]

00:54.722 --> 00:55.962
I don't see it.

00:57.725 --> 01:01.968
Are you sure you're not just jealous that
your little cousin's beating you to the altar?

01:03.355 --> 01:04.731
This isn't a competition.

01:04.898 --> 01:06.604
Then why are you keeping score?

01:08.318 --> 01:12.482
Listen, Lois, it may not kill you
to just show a little support.

01:13.907 --> 01:15.772
You want support?

01:17.119 --> 01:19.235
I'll show you support.

01:19.913 --> 01:21.164
[LOIS GRUNTS]

01:22.124 --> 01:24.911
[WHISPERS]
Oh, good idea. Here we go.

01:28.338 --> 01:31.626
Ladies and gentlemen,
my name is Lois Lane.

01:31.800 --> 01:35.634
Most of you know me as Chloe's cousin,
aka. the maid of honor.

01:35.804 --> 01:37.305
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

01:37.473 --> 01:38.679
[CHLOE LAUGHS]

01:40.434 --> 01:44.143
When Chloe and I were little girls,
we made a promise.

01:44.313 --> 01:49.023
Neither of us would get married
until we found our soul mates.

01:50.068 --> 01:54.107
The one person in the whole wide world
that we are destined to be with.

01:56.450 --> 01:58.691
Which is why you can't take
a 10-year-old on their word.

01:58.869 --> 02:00.825
[CROWD MURMURING INDISTINCTLY]

02:01.455 --> 02:03.320
Okay, come on.

02:05.292 --> 02:07.283
What I think Lois is trying to say...

02:07.461 --> 02:14.048
...is that you can't predict
when you will ﬁnd that special someone.

02:16.053 --> 02:20.012
And Jimmy is, without a doubt,
that special someone for Chloe.

02:23.060 --> 02:26.473
I've known Chloe since the 8th grade...

02:26.897 --> 02:29.104
...and we've been through a lot together.

02:29.608 --> 02:33.226
In all those years,
the truth is I've never seen her so happy.

02:36.865 --> 02:39.242
Congratulations. To Jimmy and Chloe.

02:39.409 --> 02:41.661
ALL:
To Jimmy and Chloe.

02:41.829 --> 02:44.036
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

02:45.874 --> 02:47.330
CHLOE:
We'll see you in a few months.

02:47.501 --> 02:49.116
Thank you so much. You guys are great.

02:49.294 --> 02:51.285
CHLOE: Thanks. Bye.
JIMMY: Bye.

02:51.547 --> 02:54.254
You know, it's a shame your parents
couldn't be here today.

02:54.424 --> 02:57.882
I would have really loved to celebrate
your impeccable taste with them.

02:58.053 --> 03:02.513
Well, they send their love. Dad is this close
to closing a big deal in London.

03:02.683 --> 03:05.550
His, uh, priorities are a little out of whack,
but he means well.

03:05.727 --> 03:08.184
I still hope you enjoyed yourself tonight.

03:08.355 --> 03:10.596
You know what was my favorite part
of the evening?

03:10.774 --> 03:14.687
-If you say Lois' toast, I'm getting a prenup.
-God, no. Heh.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.277
When Clark was toasting us,
I looked at you...

03:17.447 --> 03:19.904
...and you had the most wonderful smile
on your face.

03:21.201 --> 03:24.443
You know, it really means a lot to me
that you're ﬁnally okay with Clark.

03:25.622 --> 03:28.284
Me being uptight about you and Clark
is yesterday's news.

03:28.458 --> 03:31.791
There maybe a textbook's worth of history
between the two of you...

03:32.045 --> 03:34.252
...but the future's
all Chloe and Jimmy's story.

03:40.971 --> 03:44.964
I think it's about time we head upstairs
for some much needed alone time.

03:45.517 --> 03:48.805
Oh, I think that is a fantastic idea.

03:54.359 --> 03:55.974
JIMMY:
Hey.

03:56.820 --> 03:59.653
[GRUNTING]

05:09.017 --> 05:10.518
[GRUNTS]

05:20.529 --> 05:21.644
[SIGHS]

05:22.823 --> 05:24.654
Smallville?

05:24.908 --> 05:26.193
Good afternoon, Lois.

05:27.285 --> 05:29.822
I thought you might need one of these.

05:38.463 --> 05:40.203
Please, tell me we didn't....

05:48.765 --> 05:50.266
[CH UCKLES]

05:50.434 --> 05:53.346
You're hysterical
when you're hung-over, Lois.

05:54.104 --> 05:55.219
Don't worry...

05:56.106 --> 05:57.767
...you got changed all by yourself.

05:58.608 --> 06:01.145
In the middle of the kitchen,
for like an hour.

06:03.947 --> 06:04.936
[G ROANS]

06:09.286 --> 06:12.153
I take it I took a little drive
on the porcelain highway.

06:12.748 --> 06:14.784
It was more like a cross-country trip.

06:15.917 --> 06:16.906
[G ROANS]

06:18.128 --> 06:20.119
LOIS:
You know, I get--

06:20.297 --> 06:21.582
[SIGHS]

06:22.966 --> 06:24.627
You didn't have to take care of me.

06:24.801 --> 06:27.008
I would've been perfectly ﬁne
on my own at the Talon.

06:27.345 --> 06:31.509
I don't think Jimmy and Chloe would have
been up for the Whitesnake sing-along.

06:35.145 --> 06:36.134
Chloe.

06:37.856 --> 06:42.225
Uh, I was supposed to meet her
for a dress ﬁtting ﬁrst thing this morning.

06:42.402 --> 06:43.608
Do you need a ride?

06:43.987 --> 06:45.773
You may have held my hair...

06:45.947 --> 06:48.324
...but I don't need you
to hold my hand, Smallville.

06:48.492 --> 06:51.029
This may shock you,
but I can still drive a car.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.527
Not if it's not here.

06:54.748 --> 06:58.832
This may shock you, but you were in no
condition to get behind the wheel last night.

06:59.169 --> 07:00.249
[SIGHS]

07:01.421 --> 07:03.503
Thanks for the ride?

07:08.303 --> 07:09.668
[ELEVATOR BELL RINGS]

07:09.846 --> 07:12.223
What do you mean
you can't ﬁnd the IP address?

07:12.390 --> 07:14.221
The e-mail came through a ghost router.

07:14.392 --> 07:17.555
As soon as we saw it,
the router vanished from the grid.

07:17.729 --> 07:20.641
At the very least,
this could prove Mr. Luthor is still alive.

07:20.816 --> 07:23.182
Or it could prove
that someone is toying with me.

07:23.360 --> 07:27.353
Find out who took the crystal.
Or ﬁnd a new line of work.

07:30.909 --> 07:35.198
You know what's amazing to me?
You can't ﬁnd time to return my calls...

07:35.372 --> 07:37.579
...but you do manage
to ﬁt it into your busy schedule...

07:37.749 --> 07:40.707
...to buy the Star City Towers
right out from under me.

07:41.795 --> 07:44.207
Business is business.

07:44.756 --> 07:46.542
Well, this is not about business.

07:46.716 --> 07:51.676
And to be honest with you,
revenge is not your best color.

07:51.847 --> 07:55.431
Don't ﬂatter yourself. One of the most
important things that Lex taught me...

07:55.600 --> 07:57.591
...is you can't afford to live in the past.

07:57.769 --> 08:01.432
Did Professor Luthor also teach you
about deception? Or how about obsession?

08:01.606 --> 08:03.437
I hear his class in murder's an easy A.

08:03.733 --> 08:06.349
He's done more for this world
than you ever will, Oliver.

08:06.528 --> 08:09.565
He dedicated his life
to making it a safer place.

08:12.784 --> 08:15.025
You know, Mercer, it seems to me...

08:15.203 --> 08:18.411
...like Lex may have been
a little bit more than a mentor.

08:21.835 --> 08:25.453
If you're done wasting my time,
I have phone calls to make.

08:30.385 --> 08:33.548
Look, uh, I'm sorry.

08:34.848 --> 08:36.930
Really, I didn't come here
to battle with you.

08:37.767 --> 08:40.429
Actually, I came here
to raise the white ﬂag.

08:40.687 --> 08:42.393
How civil.

08:42.564 --> 08:44.930
What do you propose, a truce?

08:45.442 --> 08:48.058
Well, truce, yeah...

08:48.236 --> 08:50.101
...over dinner.

08:52.782 --> 08:54.443
You haven't changed one bit.

08:54.618 --> 08:57.576
Oliver always wants
what Oliver can't have.

08:58.663 --> 09:00.654
You know,
sometimes a meal's just a meal.

09:04.794 --> 09:06.750
You can pick me up at 7.

09:07.464 --> 09:09.455
Seven thirty it is.

09:20.310 --> 09:22.175
Chloe.

09:22.646 --> 09:23.761
Jimmy.

09:23.939 --> 09:27.147
You know what Lois likes to see
when she comes home? Pants.

09:27.317 --> 09:29.399
Pants on everyone.

09:37.160 --> 09:40.072
I had no idea Jimmy was so romantic.

09:41.873 --> 09:43.329
[LOIS CHUCKLES]

09:46.670 --> 09:49.958
Guess the Olsen's not so wholesome.

10:00.350 --> 10:03.934
LOIS [ON ANSWERING MACHINE]: Chloe,
it's your coz. Guess who came to my rescue.

10:04.104 --> 10:07.346
Not Oliver Queen. Heh. Clark Kent.

10:07.732 --> 10:10.144
He is just the sweetest boy
I have ever known-

10:10.735 --> 10:13.021
Chalk that one up to alcohol poisoning.

10:14.572 --> 10:16.984
MAN [ON ANSWERING MACHINE]:
This is Smallville P. D. Impound...

10:17.158 --> 10:18.819
...for Chloe Sullivan and James Olsen.

10:18.994 --> 10:21.861
Your vehicles were just brought in
for obstructing a street cleaner.

10:22.038 --> 10:23.448
You have 90 day-

10:23.623 --> 10:26.035
They didn't even come home last night?

10:27.210 --> 10:28.541
Then where the hell are they?

10:33.466 --> 10:35.252
[MICE SQUEAKING]

10:37.929 --> 10:40.671
[G ROANING]

10:40.849 --> 10:43.807
Chloe. Are you okay?

10:44.185 --> 10:47.052
I think so. Where are we?

10:47.230 --> 10:49.061
MAN:
Dearly beloved...

10:49.232 --> 10:55.068
...we are gathered here today to ﬁnd out
if these two were truly meant to be.

10:56.406 --> 10:57.566
[GASPS]

11:13.923 --> 11:18.007
Lois, I checked the Metropolis and the
Smallville hospitals, as well as the airport.

11:18.178 --> 11:20.840
-No sign of Jimmy or Chloe.
-You covered a lot of ground.

11:21.014 --> 11:23.756
You need to ﬁnd the right people to ask.
You ﬁnd anything?

11:23.933 --> 11:26.140
Chloe and Jimmy
aren't the only couple missing, Clark.

11:26.311 --> 11:29.474
At least three couples in the last two weeks
have vanished without a trace.

11:29.647 --> 11:32.024
-Al| engaged?
-Credit cards haven't been touched.

11:32.192 --> 11:35.104
Phone records show no sign of activity.
The list goes on and on.

11:35.278 --> 11:37.610
So unless Oprah said
eloping was in for fall—

11:37.781 --> 11:39.396
They've all been abducted.

11:40.450 --> 11:45.114
I called the police, they won't even declare
Jimmy and Chloe missing for 24 hours.

11:48.875 --> 11:52.788
What kind of person would prey on people
during the happiest time of their lives?

11:52.962 --> 11:55.294
If I hadn't been too drunk
to go home last night...

11:55.465 --> 11:59.083
-...I would have been there to stop it.
-Or you would have been missing too.

12:01.304 --> 12:02.919
Don't worry, Lois. We'll ﬁnd them.

12:03.932 --> 12:06.469
We should cross-reference Jimmy and Chloe
with the other victims.

12:06.643 --> 12:08.304
See if they have anything in common.

12:08.478 --> 12:11.345
One step ahead of you.
Jimmy, Chloe and the other couples...

12:11.523 --> 12:14.481
...all visited the same wedding vendors
within the last 10 days.

12:14.651 --> 12:17.142
A bakery, a jewelry store
and a stationery shop.

12:17.320 --> 12:18.309
To name a few.

12:18.488 --> 12:21.571
That stationery shop is around the corner.
I'm gonna check it out.

12:21.741 --> 12:24.983
-l'|l call if I ﬁnd anything.
-No way am I putting my cousin's life...

12:25.161 --> 12:27.698
...in the hands of a mild-mannered
copy boy. Keep up.

12:42.178 --> 12:44.214
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

12:48.184 --> 12:50.891
MAN: The art of abduction
is surprisingly difﬁcult.

12:51.104 --> 12:53.720
It's easier when I ﬁnd couples together.

12:54.149 --> 12:56.185
Saves time.

12:56.568 --> 12:58.433
Well, we'd hate to inconvenience you.

12:58.611 --> 13:02.320
It's no trouble at all. It's my duty.

13:03.741 --> 13:06.869
JIMMY: What—? What is that?
MAN: This is a lie detector.

13:07.036 --> 13:10.403
It's fairly harmless
and not complicated at all.

13:11.207 --> 13:16.327
In fact, when you get right down
to it, it's really quite simple.

13:16.546 --> 13:18.878
All it does is listen to your heart.

13:19.048 --> 13:21.630
I guess you expect us to believe
that's harmless too.

13:21.801 --> 13:25.043
No. This is electricity.

13:25.221 --> 13:27.428
Electricity hurts.

13:29.225 --> 13:32.888
Is this how you get your kicks?
Torturing innocent people?

13:35.565 --> 13:37.556
It's not torture.

13:37.901 --> 13:40.313
I'm doing you a favor.

13:42.071 --> 13:44.653
Not everyone is meant to be married.

13:45.742 --> 13:47.903
Countless couples rush headlong
into marriage.

13:48.077 --> 13:49.863
Ignorant to responsibility...

13:50.038 --> 13:53.951
...to the burden of truth
that comes with that level of commitment.

13:58.588 --> 14:03.503
Those that are truly dedicated
have no secrets.

14:09.557 --> 14:12.264
Let's warm up with an easy question.

14:12.602 --> 14:14.058
James...

14:14.938 --> 14:16.803
[ELECTRICITY POWERING UP]

14:16.981 --> 14:19.188
...have you ever cheated
on your ﬁancée before?

14:27.283 --> 14:28.693
No.

14:30.119 --> 14:31.279
[G ROANING]

14:31.454 --> 14:34.912
Stop! Don't hurt her!
I'm the one that lied! You hurt me!

14:35.083 --> 14:38.996
Lies don't hurt you.
Lies hurt the ones you love.

14:39.170 --> 14:40.626
[GASPING]

14:41.631 --> 14:43.792
You be honest.

14:47.679 --> 14:50.796
It wasn't really cheating.
I mean, this crazy woman, she kissed me.

14:50.974 --> 14:53.886
I had a freaking heart attack,
and I wound up in the hospital.

14:54.269 --> 14:57.352
I know. I know it wasn't your fault.

14:58.147 --> 15:00.524
You are the only girl...

15:01.484 --> 15:03.645
...l've ever loved.

15:05.196 --> 15:06.857
MAN:
That will do for now.

15:08.241 --> 15:11.699
Let's see what the bride has to say.

15:14.789 --> 15:16.529
I wonder...

15:18.167 --> 15:21.000
...how many lies is she hiding behind.

15:21.629 --> 15:23.165
[GASPING]

15:29.596 --> 15:32.588
If this were the last place on Earth,
and I had to write an SOS...

15:32.765 --> 15:36.178
-...I wouldn't come for a nib or a quill.
-Thank you for your time.

15:36.352 --> 15:39.936
Lois, we're not gonna get anywhere
if you shake down every person we talk to.

15:40.106 --> 15:43.018
He was stonewalling us. Put the screws
to a perp when the clock is ticking.

15:43.192 --> 15:44.181
[CAR HONKING]

15:44.360 --> 15:47.352
He was 70. He spent the night
in the hospital. He still had his bracelet on.

15:47.530 --> 15:49.771
Clark, my cousin, your best friend,
is missing.

15:49.949 --> 15:52.110
She could be hurt or dying or worse.

15:52.285 --> 15:54.651
Which is exactly why
we can't waste any more time.

15:54.829 --> 15:59.414
-Okay, genius, what do you wanna do?
-You should go back to the Daily Planet.

15:59.584 --> 16:02.041
See if those background checks
we ordered came in.

16:02.211 --> 16:04.873
What do you plan on doing alone
that we can't do together?

16:05.548 --> 16:06.537
A lot.

16:09.927 --> 16:12.794
Wait a minute.
The guy is preying on couples, right?

16:14.182 --> 16:16.924
-No, don't even go there.
-If we walk in there pretending...

16:17.101 --> 16:19.763
...to be the bait,
we'll have him eating out of our hands.

16:19.937 --> 16:22.223
No one will believe it.
Not even for a second.

16:24.400 --> 16:26.436
Clark Kent...

16:27.070 --> 16:28.731
...will you marry me?

16:36.746 --> 16:38.782
A smile every now and then
wouldn't kill you.

16:38.956 --> 16:41.447
In short supply, Lois.
I wouldn't wanna waste one.

16:41.626 --> 16:42.741
Can I help you?

16:43.419 --> 16:49.380
Well, we are ﬁnally out ring shopping.
Who's the luckiest girl in the world? I am.

16:49.550 --> 16:53.418
Friends of ours said your store is the best
place in town to ﬁnd engagement rings.

16:53.596 --> 16:55.587
Is there a certain piece you'd like to see?

16:56.099 --> 16:57.430
Well....

16:59.268 --> 17:02.886
-What about this one, pumpkin?
-Anything you want, mufﬁn.

17:03.147 --> 17:05.763
Must be great, seeing happy couples
come here every day.

17:05.942 --> 17:06.931
It certainly is.

17:07.110 --> 17:11.103
It's very fulﬁlling helping to solidify
the bond between husband and wife.

17:11.280 --> 17:13.612
Excellent craftsmanship.

17:13.783 --> 17:17.696
A perfect circle,
no beginning and no end.

17:18.413 --> 17:20.119
Try it on. See how it looks.

17:23.459 --> 17:26.951
Don't get stage fright, poodle.
You're gonna have to do this center stage...

17:27.130 --> 17:29.496
...in front of a packed house
sooner than you think.

17:29.966 --> 17:31.297
He has performance anxiety.

17:31.467 --> 17:32.843
[CH UCKLES]

17:35.763 --> 17:38.470
Look at that. A perfect ﬁt.

17:49.152 --> 17:50.642
What are you two doing here?

17:50.820 --> 17:54.108
Oliver, uh, didn't get the invitation yet?

17:55.032 --> 17:56.988
Invitation to what?

17:58.119 --> 17:59.780
Tell him, cupcake.

18:04.041 --> 18:06.327
Lois and I are....

18:08.171 --> 18:09.331
We're getting married.

18:09.756 --> 18:11.337
[LAUGHS]

18:18.931 --> 18:21.843
You're just full of surprises lately,
aren't you, Clark?

18:22.018 --> 18:23.178
I know, right?

18:23.352 --> 18:27.812
I mean, we've been friends for so long,
but we just had this, um, one magical night.

18:27.982 --> 18:30.724
And we couldn't
deny our feelings any longer.

18:33.529 --> 18:35.485
Is this true?

18:36.240 --> 18:37.855
I'm afraid so.

18:45.333 --> 18:47.369
See you at the wedding.

18:54.717 --> 18:58.255
She has great taste.
You're a very lucky man.

18:58.429 --> 19:00.385
You have no idea.

19:00.681 --> 19:02.808
If you're this afraid
of pretend commitment...

19:02.975 --> 19:06.433
...what's gonna happen when some girl
makes the mistake of falling for you?

19:06.938 --> 19:08.929
This isn't working. We need to split up.

19:09.106 --> 19:11.688
We can track down more leads
if we go in opposite directions.

19:11.859 --> 19:14.396
-What if you get into trouble?
-I think I'll be okay.

19:14.570 --> 19:17.562
You know, you're drifting
dangerously close to cocky.

19:17.740 --> 19:21.358
What, no snarky comeback
from the peanut gallery?

19:23.454 --> 19:24.489
[SIGHS]

19:27.333 --> 19:28.368
Please don't do this.

19:28.543 --> 19:30.499
MAN: You should be pleading with me
to continue.

19:30.670 --> 19:33.582
If only someone had taken the time
to do this for my wife and I.

19:33.756 --> 19:35.257
You hook her up to your machine?

19:35.424 --> 19:37.585
Something tells
me she didn't walk out of here.

19:37.760 --> 19:40.422
I cherished her, James. I honored her.

19:40.596 --> 19:42.803
I did everything I promised
when I took my wedding vows.

19:42.974 --> 19:46.637
And how does she reward me?
With one lie after another.

19:49.939 --> 19:51.930
She never knew...

19:52.358 --> 19:53.973
...but I could smell him on her.

19:56.028 --> 19:57.814
So you killed her.

20:00.408 --> 20:04.742
You see, the heart and the mouth
are not always on the same page.

20:10.334 --> 20:11.744
Get the hell away from her.

20:12.295 --> 20:13.284
[ELECTRICITY POWERING UP]

20:13.462 --> 20:15.202
Chloe...

20:16.382 --> 20:18.748
...have you ever cheated on your ﬁancé?

20:20.219 --> 20:21.254
No.

20:24.223 --> 20:27.181
Excellent. Next question.

20:29.353 --> 20:32.140
Are you in love with anyone else?

20:33.983 --> 20:36.816
Don't answer him, Chloe.
Don't give him the satisfaction.

20:37.486 --> 20:39.317
[G ROANS]

20:39.488 --> 20:40.523
lib}

20:43.492 --> 20:49.829
Your ﬁancé is not the best person
to be taking advice from at this moment.

20:51.417 --> 20:54.329
Now, I'm gonna ask you one more time.

20:57.048 --> 21:00.836
Are you in love with anyone else?

21:08.351 --> 21:09.841
No.

21:13.022 --> 21:15.729
[GASPING]

21:22.198 --> 21:26.191
Only you, Jimmy. Forever.

21:29.330 --> 21:30.945
[CH UCKLES]

21:35.044 --> 21:39.162
Congratulations,
James Olsen, Chloe Sullivan.

21:39.632 --> 21:42.248
I now pronounce you husband and wife.

21:48.724 --> 21:50.464
Mercy.

21:50.935 --> 21:54.177
We got dinner reservations at Hob's Bay
in just under an hour.

21:57.191 --> 21:58.727
I like to work up an appetite.

21:58.901 --> 22:00.892
[GRUNTING]

22:03.322 --> 22:04.437
[CH UCKLES]

22:05.741 --> 22:06.947
You used to be better at this.

22:07.118 --> 22:10.076
What happened to not being interested
in revenge?

22:11.038 --> 22:14.280
This is not revenge. This is just practice.

22:14.458 --> 22:17.291
Weak men like you make me stronger.

22:25.678 --> 22:28.795
So you learn that Lionel killed your parents,
and what do you do?

22:29.390 --> 22:32.427
You drink yourself onto the society page.
For what? Like, a month?

22:32.601 --> 22:35.764
Well, you know me,
I like to keep myself busy.

22:35.938 --> 22:40.398
You still can't take anything seriously,
can you? Just like our relationship.

22:40.568 --> 22:42.399
[GRUNTING]

22:42.570 --> 22:44.401
You know how much you meant to me.

22:44.572 --> 22:47.405
Yeah, that became clear
when I caught you with the waitress.

22:50.369 --> 22:51.950
Or was she a hostess?

22:53.330 --> 22:56.322
-How many times do I have to apologize?
-I don't want an apology.

22:59.253 --> 23:00.584
I want an explanation.

23:07.386 --> 23:09.877
What the hell were you so afraid of?

23:15.394 --> 23:16.474
You.

23:30.743 --> 23:32.608
Clark, it's Lois.

23:32.787 --> 23:37.656
I spoke with the police,
and they told me that I think I should, uh—

23:38.417 --> 23:43.161
Do you mind? Your high beams
are burning holes into my skull.

23:44.215 --> 23:45.671
I don't know what to do anymore.

23:45.841 --> 23:49.129
Can you give me a call
as soon as you get this? Bye.

23:49.303 --> 23:51.168
MAN:
You'll be seeing your ﬁancé soon enough.

23:55.267 --> 23:57.349
Son of a bitch.

24:20.292 --> 24:22.123
Oh, my God.

24:22.336 --> 24:25.999
Jimmy. Jimmy, wake up.

24:27.341 --> 24:28.877
We're okay.

24:29.051 --> 24:30.416
What the hell happened?

24:30.594 --> 24:34.212
Last thing I remember, that guy pulled out
that gun and everything went black.

24:34.390 --> 24:36.631
I told you we'd make it out.

24:40.938 --> 24:45.432
Is this that masked man's idea
of some kind of a twisted joke?

24:45.693 --> 24:49.561
Uh, I'm gonna have to take the credit
for this one.

24:50.489 --> 24:54.653
And for the record,
it was all a lot less creepy yesterday.

24:56.203 --> 25:01.243
You know, I don't think I'd still be alive if I
was sitting across anyone else in that room.

25:02.918 --> 25:04.749
Because we're meant to be together?

25:04.920 --> 25:09.380
Because things like that
don't happen to people by accident.

25:11.427 --> 25:13.133
No.

25:13.345 --> 25:16.257
Because you don't have any secrets.

25:27.067 --> 25:29.274
We should call the sheriff.

25:31.280 --> 25:32.770
Okay.

25:34.074 --> 25:35.405
[POLICE SIREN WAILS]

25:35.576 --> 25:38.943
OFFICER: And if you hear anything again
just get ahold of us.

25:41.040 --> 25:42.905
We appreciate your help.

25:43.083 --> 25:45.540
-l'm glad you two are okay.
-C|ark, what is it?

25:45.711 --> 25:49.374
Lois. I can't ﬁnd her. She left me a
voicemail, then never made it to the Planet.

25:49.548 --> 25:51.459
She was saying something
about car headlights.

25:51.634 --> 25:54.000
Headlights?
That's what he used when he took us.

25:54.178 --> 25:56.169
-Why would he want Lois?
-lt's a long story.

25:56.347 --> 25:59.134
But anything you can remember
might help me ﬁnd Lois.

25:59.308 --> 26:01.173
Uh, this guy,
he's a certiﬁable wack job, C.K.

26:01.352 --> 26:03.343
He was talking about how secrets kill.

26:03.520 --> 26:09.311
-And our bond.
-Stuff about lies begetting lies.

26:09.485 --> 26:11.021
What did he say about your bond?

26:11.737 --> 26:15.605
I don't know. Uh, he was talking about
how important it is...

26:15.783 --> 26:18.946
...to solidify the bond
between husband and wife.

26:22.623 --> 26:24.659
I know who has Lois.

26:32.007 --> 26:35.716
LOIS: Tell me right now,
what did you do with my cousin?

26:36.804 --> 26:38.760
Where is she?

26:44.311 --> 26:45.847
Lois?

26:47.564 --> 26:50.021
-Lois.
-Clark.

26:50.192 --> 26:53.525
-You gotta ﬁnd Chloe and Jimmy.
-He let them go. I'm gonna get you out.

26:53.696 --> 26:57.188
-But you need to tell me, where is he?
MAN: Right behind you.

26:58.492 --> 27:00.153
Clark.

27:02.204 --> 27:03.444
[G ROANING]

27:11.672 --> 27:13.128
LOIS:
Clark?

27:14.091 --> 27:15.877
Wake up.

27:19.596 --> 27:21.211
Clark.

27:21.640 --> 27:23.346
Clark.

27:24.268 --> 27:26.133
Wake up.

27:40.034 --> 27:42.241
CLARK:
I know who you are!

27:46.290 --> 27:49.407
Then I suppose
I won't be needing this anymore.

27:50.336 --> 27:52.577
Now that we're all acquainted.

27:53.005 --> 27:54.211
Let's begin.

27:54.631 --> 27:56.087
What's the point?

27:56.258 --> 27:59.091
Now that we've both seen your face,
you're gonna kill us anyway.

27:59.261 --> 28:01.377
Don't be so certain.

28:02.556 --> 28:06.845
You must really care about her
storming in here.

28:07.936 --> 28:09.722
It's very gallant of you.

28:09.897 --> 28:12.263
Yeah, he's stupid that way.

28:15.152 --> 28:18.064
-Let her go.
-After her turn, you'll get yours.

28:18.238 --> 28:20.103
My turn?

28:20.324 --> 28:22.906
What is this, some kind of game?

28:23.535 --> 28:24.570
No.

28:24.745 --> 28:26.610
No, it's a test.

28:26.789 --> 28:30.327
To reveal how much you two
have been hiding from one another.

28:31.460 --> 28:35.248
If you pass, you'll want to invite me
to your wedding.

28:36.215 --> 28:38.126
If you fail...

28:40.094 --> 28:43.052
...well, the guest list
will be the least of your worries.

28:46.225 --> 28:48.181
Ladies ﬁrst.

28:48.727 --> 28:51.184
Have you ever cheated on your ﬁancé?

28:57.111 --> 28:59.602
Of course not. Don't be ridiculous.

29:00.030 --> 29:01.486
[SHOUTING]

29:01.657 --> 29:03.113
What are you doing?

29:03.283 --> 29:05.069
You're killing him!

29:06.995 --> 29:09.407
No. Your lies are.

29:09.581 --> 29:12.288
Okay, okay. I take it back then. I'm sorry.

29:12.459 --> 29:15.622
Just don't hurt him again.

29:16.171 --> 29:17.707
[CLARK GASPING]

29:29.685 --> 29:31.425
CLARK:
Killing us...

29:31.687 --> 29:34.099
...it won't take away the pain
that pushed you here.

29:34.273 --> 29:36.855
I'm doing this for you.

29:37.025 --> 29:38.686
What?

29:39.194 --> 29:42.186
The broken-hearted are the walking dead.

29:42.364 --> 29:46.778
Either way, I'm saving you both
a lot of unnecessary pain.

29:47.369 --> 29:50.907
Okay, crazy, this is the deal.

29:51.290 --> 29:54.032
We're not even really a couple.

29:54.710 --> 29:57.793
So this twisted test
doesn't mean anything.

30:01.717 --> 30:03.673
Next question.

30:05.554 --> 30:09.638
Deep down, underneath it all,
do you love this man?

30:13.812 --> 30:16.224
Answer the question, Lois.

30:18.066 --> 30:20.102
Don't outthink it.

30:21.487 --> 30:23.273
Just tell the truth.

30:28.660 --> 30:29.740
[SIGHS]

30:34.583 --> 30:36.198
Do you love him?

30:42.424 --> 30:44.380
Tell the truth.

30:51.725 --> 30:54.762
MAN:
Do you love him?

30:57.272 --> 30:58.648
[SOBBING]

31:04.947 --> 31:06.153
Yes.

31:16.917 --> 31:18.032
[SIGHS]

31:25.634 --> 31:27.295
And you...

31:28.178 --> 31:29.588
...do you love this woman?

31:36.603 --> 31:39.811
Speak up. She can't hear you
if you don't speak up.

32:01.545 --> 32:02.785
[GRUNTING]

32:08.510 --> 32:09.590
[SIGHS]

32:10.095 --> 32:11.130
CLARK:
Lois.

32:13.515 --> 32:15.346
-Clark?
-Lois, are you okay?

32:15.642 --> 32:16.631
Hmm.

32:17.728 --> 32:19.514
I'm not sure.

32:22.733 --> 32:24.644
Let's get you out of here.

32:40.709 --> 32:44.873
The one person in the whole wide world
that we were destined to be with.

32:45.047 --> 32:46.583
Which is why you can't take a--

32:46.757 --> 32:49.464
Yeah, that's pretty much how I felt.

32:49.760 --> 32:52.342
Oh, my God, Chloe, I am so sorry.

32:52.512 --> 32:55.049
I know my face is under "faux pas"
in the dictionary...

32:55.223 --> 32:57.555
...but this is a whole new low.

32:57.726 --> 32:59.682
I would say that this is a close second...

32:59.853 --> 33:02.390
...behind the time you crashed
Lana's engagement party.

33:02.564 --> 33:06.182
In fact, you may wanna start avoiding
engagement parties altogether.

33:06.360 --> 33:07.395
[LOIS SIGHS]

33:08.904 --> 33:12.692
Chloe, it's not funny.
I ruined your special night.

33:13.325 --> 33:17.364
Lois, considering how the night ended,
I'd say the party was a rousing success.

33:17.537 --> 33:19.277
Besides, you were just being honest...

33:19.456 --> 33:23.040
...though you could have been
a little less public about it.

33:23.752 --> 33:26.915
Lois, why didn't you just tell me
that this is how you felt?

33:28.882 --> 33:30.713
I don't know.

33:30.884 --> 33:33.751
Look, Clark and Lana went south.

33:33.929 --> 33:36.921
Things fell apart between me and Ollie.

33:37.974 --> 33:42.308
Just knowing that I had everything
that I wanted right in front of me...

33:42.938 --> 33:45.520
...and having it slip away.

33:46.608 --> 33:50.226
I just didn't want to see you
have that kind of heartache.

33:51.655 --> 33:56.615
Lois, you are the most wonderful big cousin
in the world for thinking that.

33:56.993 --> 34:01.657
But trust me, I wouldn't have said yes
if I didn't know it was meant to be.

34:02.666 --> 34:04.873
How can you be sure?

34:06.128 --> 34:12.215
Because when I look at Jimmy,
I can just feel it, in my heart.

34:12.592 --> 34:15.174
I mean, sunset or dungeon, he's my guy.

34:16.805 --> 34:17.794
Wow.

34:18.682 --> 34:20.718
Color me jealous.

34:22.269 --> 34:24.305
Clark was right after all.

34:25.564 --> 34:28.522
He usually is. Get used to it.

34:28.692 --> 34:30.432
JIMMY:
Get used to what?

34:37.993 --> 34:39.358
[LOIS SIGHING]

34:41.496 --> 34:43.908
To being a member of the family.

34:44.082 --> 34:46.414
Congratulations, Jimmy.

34:47.919 --> 34:49.329
What was that all about?

34:49.504 --> 34:52.166
You and me, oddly enough.

34:52.340 --> 34:55.582
Speaking of which,
I have something you need to see.

34:56.386 --> 34:57.922
After the Spanish Inquisition...

34:58.096 --> 35:01.509
...l was thinking we deserve
an extra-long honeymoon.

35:01.683 --> 35:06.677
-So maybe Bora Bora? Saint Tropez?
JIMMY: Chloe.

35:07.731 --> 35:10.518
Before you start booking,
there's something you need to know.

35:13.153 --> 35:15.815
As insane as that guy was,
he made a great point.

35:15.989 --> 35:17.980
If we're gonna make it...

35:18.366 --> 35:20.823
...we can't have any secrets
from each other anymore.

35:21.870 --> 35:24.361
Yeah, but if the last 12 hours
have proven anything...

35:24.539 --> 35:26.621
...it's that we don't have
much left to hide.

35:29.377 --> 35:32.210
Yeah, there is.

35:34.049 --> 35:36.631
I'm not who you think I am.

35:39.888 --> 35:41.753
The sudden knot in my stomach
tells me...

35:41.932 --> 35:45.140
...this isn't you embracing
your inner Nietzsche.

35:51.942 --> 35:53.898
They, uh....

35:54.528 --> 35:56.940
Well, they actually don't exist.

35:57.113 --> 36:01.322
Well, I mean, they do. Of course they do.
They exist. It's just that--

36:02.077 --> 36:05.410
My dad's not an investment banker
in Manhattan.

36:07.541 --> 36:11.500
He's a part-time mechanic
and full-time alcoholic in Oklahoma City.

36:12.921 --> 36:15.003
I never even really met my mom.

36:19.177 --> 36:22.044
Why would you keep
something like this from me?

36:25.225 --> 36:27.807
This city, it's huge.

36:27.978 --> 36:30.560
It's the top of the world
coming from where I come from.

36:30.730 --> 36:33.392
And the only way I could ﬁt in...

36:35.110 --> 36:36.520
...was to be someone else.

36:40.115 --> 36:42.731
Why didn't you trust me?

36:44.953 --> 36:46.489
I know.

36:47.038 --> 36:48.778
I'm
sorry

36:49.332 --> 36:51.789
I'm so sorry.

36:53.003 --> 36:54.209
I screwed up bigtime.

36:54.379 --> 36:58.122
And I totally understand
if you need some time or even if—

36:58.300 --> 36:59.460
If you want out.

37:02.804 --> 37:04.965
A guy like me...

37:05.932 --> 37:08.264
...doesn't get a girl like you, Chloe.

37:10.854 --> 37:14.563
Life, it doesn't work like that.

37:19.154 --> 37:21.110
Yeah, it does.

37:55.523 --> 37:58.060
So much for breakfast in bed.

37:59.027 --> 38:01.484
I'm late for a meeting in Metropolis.

38:01.655 --> 38:03.691
Some of us still have corporations to run.

38:03.865 --> 38:07.028
Oh, that's right. I forgot.
Although I've got this funny feeling...

38:07.202 --> 38:10.365
...that you could probably ﬁnd
somebody else to answer your phones.

38:10.538 --> 38:16.579
I'm thinking more like, um, dinner in Malibu
in time for the sunset. What do you say?

38:17.712 --> 38:20.624
Is that a hint of romance I detect?

38:22.425 --> 38:24.677
I can't stop myself.

38:35.939 --> 38:37.520
Save it...

38:37.691 --> 38:39.852
...in case you wanna tip another hostess.

38:43.071 --> 38:45.653
There was nothing romantic
about last night, Oliver.

38:45.824 --> 38:49.282
I had an itch. You scratched it.

38:55.417 --> 38:57.624
Tess, what happened to you?

39:01.923 --> 39:03.754
I grew up.

39:05.218 --> 39:08.881
And you left right when things started
to get interesting.

39:10.390 --> 39:11.926
You know the way out.

39:32.287 --> 39:33.493
[SIGHS]

39:33.663 --> 39:35.779
CLARK:
You're not avoiding me, are you?

39:37.917 --> 39:39.453
Me? Why would I be avoiding you?

39:39.627 --> 39:42.494
I was just shopping for wedding gifts
for Chloe and Jimmy.

39:42.672 --> 39:45.414
So you're ﬁnally onboard
with the happy couple.

39:45.592 --> 39:49.301
Yup. All it took was them passing
a madman's electric-cosmo death quiz...

39:49.471 --> 39:50.586
...and I am sold.

39:50.764 --> 39:52.049
[ELEVATOR BELL RINGS]

39:54.809 --> 39:56.185
In or out?

39:57.145 --> 40:00.387
You know, all things considered,
stairs are better for cardio.

40:00.982 --> 40:04.975
Come on. Statistically,
this is the safer way to travel.

40:19.000 --> 40:21.161
He confessed. The jeweler.

40:22.337 --> 40:24.248
I heard. Five couples?

40:28.134 --> 40:29.249
[SIGHS]

40:30.011 --> 40:32.002
So, uh, about that test....

40:33.890 --> 40:35.005
Um.

40:39.521 --> 40:41.978
Who would have thought
you were such a good liar, huh?

40:42.148 --> 40:45.140
I mean, you even beat that machine.

40:45.693 --> 40:48.935
Even though I'm a natural
master of deception, I needed a little help.

40:49.114 --> 40:52.231
I mean, that machine was a piece
of kaiser-era junk.

40:52.408 --> 40:53.534
[CH UCKLES]

40:54.119 --> 40:57.953
I mean, it did work the ﬁrst time,
you know, when you electrocuted me.

40:58.581 --> 41:00.572
Exactly.

41:00.917 --> 41:05.536
While he was off playing game-show host,
I slipped the sensor off my ﬁnger.

41:05.713 --> 41:07.795
Pretty crafty, huh?

41:10.051 --> 41:12.542
So you weren't telling the truth.

41:14.055 --> 41:17.297
Please. I mean, we do make a good team.

41:17.475 --> 41:20.512
But don't let our cover
go to that big old head of yours.

41:20.937 --> 41:22.302
[SCOFFS]

41:22.564 --> 41:24.225
I didn't.

41:25.733 --> 41:27.985
-Good.
-Great.

41:30.280 --> 41:31.360
[ELEVATOR BELL RINGS]

41:34.242 --> 41:37.109
Let's just be happy
that I was under the gun and not you.

41:37.787 --> 41:39.288
And why's that?

41:39.956 --> 41:42.447
Smallville, everyone knows
you're a terrible liar.

41:42.625 --> 41:45.287
Who knows where we'd be
if you'd answered that question?

42:29.881 --> 42:31.872
[ENGLISH SDH]
